197.title: Davao Bombing: Mga kuwento ng pag-asa - Part 1
197.plot: Roxas Night Market in Davao City is known for its massage parlors around the area. But one night in September 2016, happiness of the market goers went to a screeching halt when a bomb detonated in the area, resulting to over hundreds of casualties. Will the victims and their loved ones ever seek hope and justice amid the tragedy?

199.title: May forever sa Bahay Pag-ibig: The Jessie Tano and Tess Suarez Love Story
199.plot: Jessie and Tess grew apart together with their own families. But as they age, both of their love lives did not turn out to be fruitful as their respective families chose to put them in the house for the elderly, the "Bahay Pag-ibig." What awaits them as they cross each other's paths at a later age?

200.title: Losing Jeffrey, Finding Jayson: The Jayson Tomas Story
200.plot: At the age of 18, Liza conceived her child Jayson while working as a factory worker. As the factory shut down, she was forced to leave her son to her best friend Sabel and work in the province to seek greener pastures. But as years pass, Liza never knew that Sabel would own her child as if it was hers before fleeing. Would destiny find its way to make Jayson and Liza's ends meet eventually?

201.title: Justice for the Battered Child: The Linda Cagalitan Story
201.plot: Single mother Linda has to leave the country to work as a domestic helper abroad so she could provide for her children's needs. In an unexpected turn of events, her youngest child dies from physical abuse in the hands of the person she trusts. How will she be able to collect herself amid the toughest challenge in her life?

202.title: Ang sakripisyo ng anak: The Ramon Burce Story
202.plot: After having a typhoid at an early age, Ramon (Christian Bables) grew up with a lot of insecurities because of his inability to socialize. Despite this, he continued to work for his family to suffice their needs to make his parents (Ms. Gina Alajar and Allan Paule) proud. Tough challenges will hurdle Ramon as he grieves for his father's death, being left with her mother. Will he be able to take care of his mother without help from his siblings despite having special needs?
